{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869764921,"sessionID":"ses_285ea26e9ffeiCsnXPY05fn29X","part":{"id":"prt_d7a16198a001sPGVUyJgr0W27F","messageID":"msg_d7a15f3fe001hp36zxFONi18di","sessionID":"ses_285ea26e9ffeiCsnXPY05fn29X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fafd0bffc8aa4de49d8f023c633ab3ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: Implement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`). The pack command:\n16: \n17: 1. Validates workspace directory structure\n18: 2. Loads or creates `agent_metadata.yaml` (with fallback to `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`)\n19: 3. Merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n20: 4. Validates language compatibility (Python requires `.py` files, Java requires `pom.xml`)\n21: 5. Processes dependencies (Python: requirements.txt; Java: pom.xml)\n22: 6. Generates Dockerfile if missing (language-specific templates)\n23: 7. Updates and saves metadata with pack results\n24: 8. Reports agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path\n25: \n26: ## Out of Scope\n27: \n28: - Docker image building (handled by `build` command - AR-021)\n29: - Kubernetes deployment (handled by `publish` command - AR-022)\n30: - Agent invocation (handled by `invoke` command - AR-023)\n31: - Status checking (handled by `status` command - AR-024)\n32: - Container registry operations\n33: - Cloud build mode integration\n34: \n35: ## Dependencies\n36: \n37: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n38: |------------|---------|---------|\n39: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n40: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata model validation |\n41: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML metadata file handling |\n42: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Progress indicators and colored output |\n43: | `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Unit/integration testing |\n44: | `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mocking support for tests |\n45: \n46: ## Deliverables\n47: \n48: | File | Description |\n49: |------|-------------|\n50: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `pack` command implementation |\n51: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` class with pack workflow |\n52: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n53: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata` model, `MetadataService` |\n54: | `tests/test_pack_runtime.py` | PackRuntime unit tests |\n55: | `tests/test_pack_cli.py` | CLI pack command tests |\n56: \n57: ## Acceptance Criteria\n58: \n59: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/workspace` validates workspace structure\n60: - [ ] Creates `agent_metadata.yaml` if missing, loads from fallback files if present\n61: - [ ] CLI options (`--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`) override metadata values\n62: - [ ] Python workspace validation: requires at least one `.py` file\n63: - [ ] Java workspace validation: requires `pom.xml`\n64: - [ ] Generates Dockerfile if missing, preserves existing Dockerfile\n65: - [ ] Python Dockerfile template: `FROM python:3.10-slim`, pip install, expose port\n66: - [ ] Java Dockerfile template: Multi-stage Maven build → JRE runtime\n67: - [ ] Saves updated metadata to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n68: - [ ] Rich progress spinner during pack operation\n69: - [ ] Success output: agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path\n70: - [ ] Error output: colored error message, traceback if --verbose, exit code 1\n71: - [ ] Port validation: 1-65535 range\n72: - [ ] Language validation: 'python' or 'java' only\n73: - [ ] Build mode validation: 'local' or 'cloud' only\n74: \n75: ## References\n76: \n77: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n78: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n79: - AR-021 — CLI build command\n80: - AR-022 — CLI publish command\n81: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n82: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n\n(End of file - total 82 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`). The pack command:\n\n1. Validates workspace directory structure\n2. Loads or creates `agent_metadata.yaml` (with fallback to `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`)\n3. Merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n4. Validates language compatibility (Python requires `.py` files, Java requires `pom.xml`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/spec.md","time":{"start":1775869764890,"end":1775869764920}}}}
