es\n66: \n67: [TO BE FILLED]\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n72: \n73: [TO BE FILLED]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. Risks\n78: \n79: | Risk | Mitigation |\n80: |------|------------|\n81: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n86: \n87: [TO BE FILLED]\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 7. References\n92: \n93: [TO BE FILLED]\n\n(End of file - total 93 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-020 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define purpose and goals for CLI pack command]\n\n**Current State**: [TO BE FILLED: Describe current state]\n\n**Target State**: [TO BE FILLED: Describe target state after implementation]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869764894,"end":1775869764922}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869764926,"sessionID":"ses_285ea26e9ffeiCsnXPY05fn29X","part":{"id":"prt_d7a162114001jZFRces88kU6YJ","messageID":"msg_d7a15f3fe001hp36zxFONi18di","sessionID":"ses_285ea26e9ffeiCsnXPY05fn29X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e8ff4b0060344a74820dc89c743363a1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                           Developer Environment                          │\n24: │  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐               │\n25: │  │   Terminal   │───▶│  kubectl-    │───▶│  Workspace   │               │\n26: │  │   (CLI)      │    │  agentcube   │    │  Directory   │               │\n27: │  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘               │\n28: │                              │                                           │\n29: │                              ▼                                           │\n30: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n31: │                    │ agent_metadata.  │                                  │\n32: │                    │ yaml             │                                  │\n33: │                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n34: │                              │                                           │\n35: │                              ▼                                           │\n36: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n37: │                    │ Dockerfile       │ (generated if missing)           │\n38: │                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n39: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Component Diagram\n43: \n44: ```\n45: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n46: │                         agentcube/cli/main.py                            │\n47: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n48: │  │                        Typer App                                  │   │\n49: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  │   │\n50: │  │  │   pack()   │  │   build()  │  │  publish() │  │  invoke()  │  │   │\n51: │  │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │   │\n52: │  │  └─────┬──────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  │   │\n53: │  └───────│──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n54: │          │                                                               │\n55: └──────────│───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n56:            ▼\n57: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n58: │                      agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py                   │\n59: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n60: │  │                      PackRuntime                                  │   │\n61: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n62: │  │  │   pack()        │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_load_or_create_ │   │   │\n63: │  │  │   (main entry)  │  │workspace_        │  │metadata()       │   │   │\n64: │  │  └─────────────────┘  │structure()       │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n65: │  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n66: │  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n67: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n68: │  │  │_apply_option_   │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_process_       │   │   │\n69: │  │  │overrides()      │  │language_         │  │dependencies()   │   │   │\n70: │  │  └─────────────────┘  │compatibility()   │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n71: │  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n72: │  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n73: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n74: │  │  │_generate_       │──▶│_update_pack_    │──▶│_prepare_output_ │   │   │\n75: │  │  │dockerfile()     │  │metadata()       │  │path()           │   │   │\n76: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n77: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n78: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n79:            │\n80:            ▼\n81: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │                      agentcube/services/                                 │\n83: │  ┌───────────────────────┐        ┌───────────────────────┐            │\n84: │  │   MetadataService     │        │     DockerService     │            │\n85: │  │  (metadata_service.py)│        │  (docker_service.py)  │            │\n86: │  │  - load_metadata()    │        │  - check_docker_      │            │\n87: │  │  - save_metadata()    │        │    available()        │            │\n88: │  │  - validate_workspace │        │  - build_image()      │            │\n89: │  └───────────────────────┘        └───────────────────────┘            │\n90: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n91:            │\n92:            ▼\n93: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n94: │                      agentcube/models/pack_models.py                     │\n95: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n96: │  │                    MetadataOptions                                │   │\n97: │  │  - agent_name: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n98: │  │  - language: Optional[str] = 'python'                             │   │\n99: │  │  - entrypoint: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n100: │  │  - port: Optional[int] = 8080                                     │   │\n101: │  │  - build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'                            │   │\n102: │  │  - description: Optional[str]                                     │   │\n103: │  │  - from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])                     │   │\n104: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n105: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### Request Flow\n109: \n110: ```\n111: User                    CLI (main.py)              PackRuntime           Services\n112:  │                          │                          │                    │\n113:  │ kubectl-agentcube pack   │                          │                    │\n114:  │─────────────────────────▶│                          │                    │\n115:  │                          │ PackRuntime(verbose)     │                    │\n116:  │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n117:  │                          │                          │                    │\n118:  │                          │ pack(workspace, options) │                    │\n119:  │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n120:  │                          │                          │                    │\n121:  │                          │                          │ _validate_workspace│\n122:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n123:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n124:  │                          │                          │                    │\n125:  │                          │                          │ _load_or_create    │\n126:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n127:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n128:  │                          │                          │  AgentMetadata     │\n129:  │                          │                          │                    │\n130:  │                          │                          │ _apply_overrides   │\n131:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n132:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n133:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n134:  │                          │                          │  merged metadata   │\n135:  │                          │                          │                    │\n136:  │                          │                          │ _validate_language │\n137:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n138:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n139:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n140:  │                          │                          │                    │\n141:  │                          │                          │ _process_deps      │\n142:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n143:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n144:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n145:  │                          │                          │                    │\n146:  │                          │                          │ _generate_dockerfile\n147:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n148:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n149:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n150:  │                          │                          │  Dockerfile path   │\n151:  │                          │                          │                    │\n152:  │                          │                          │ _update_pack_metadata\n153:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n154:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n155:  │                          │                          │                    │\n156:  │                          │◀─────────────────────────│                    │\n157:  │                          │  result dict             │                    │\n158:  │                          │                          │                    │\n159:  │◀─────────────────────────│                          │                    │\n160:  │  Success message with    │                          │                    │\n161:  │  agent_name, paths       │                          │                    │\n162:  │                          │                          │                    │\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Data Structures\n168: \n169: ### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n173: from typing import Optional, Any, Dict\n174: \n175: @dataclass\n176: class MetadataOptions:\n177:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n178:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n179:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n180:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n181:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n182:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n183:     description: Optional[str] = None\n184:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n185:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n186:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n187:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n188:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n189:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n190:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n191:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n192: \n193:     @classmethod\n194:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n195:         return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None})\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### `AgentMetadata` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n202: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n203: \n204: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n205:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n206:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n207:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n208:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n209:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n210:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n211:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n212:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n213:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n214:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n215:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n216:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n217:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n218:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n219:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n220:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n221:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n222:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n223:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n224:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n225:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n226:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n227: \n228:     @field_validator('language')\n229:     @classmethod\n230:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n231:         allowed = ['python', 'java']\n232:         v_lower = v.lower()\n233:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n234:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n235:         return v_lower\n236: \n237:     @field_validator('build_mode')\n238:     @classmethod\n239:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n240:         allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n241:         v_lower = v.lower()\n242:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n243:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n244:         return v_lower\n245: \n246:     @field_validator('port')\n247:     @classmethod\n248:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n249:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n250:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n251:         return v\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: from pathlib import Path\n258: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n259: \n260: class PackRuntime:\n261:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n262:         self.verbose = verbose\n263:         self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)\n264:         self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)\n265: \n266:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n267:         result = {\n268:             \"agent_name\": None,\n269:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n270:             \"metadata_path\": None,\n271:             \"dockerfile_path\": None,\n272:             \"status\": \"pending\"\n273:         }\n274:         try:\n275:             self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n276:             metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n277:             metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n278:             self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n279:             self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n280:             dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n281:             self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n282:             output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n283:             \n284:             result[\"agent_name\"] = metadata.agent_name\n285:             result[\"metadata_path\"] = str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\")\n286:             result[\"dockerfile_path\"] = str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None\n287:             result[\"status\"] = \"success\"\n288:         except Exception as e:\n289:             result[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n290:             result[\"error\"] = str(e)\n291:             raise\n292:         return result\n293: \n294:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n295:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n296:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n297:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n298:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n299: \n300:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n301:         metadata_files = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n302:         for filename in metadata_files:\n303:             filepath = workspace_path / filename\n304:             if filepath.exists():\n305:                 return self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n306:         \n307:         agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n308:         return AgentMetadata(\n309:             agent_name=agent_name,\n310:             language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n311:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, \"python\"),\n312:             port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n313:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n314:             description=options.get(\"description\", \"\")\n315:         )\n316: \n317:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n318:         updates = {}\n319:         if options.get(\"agent_name\"):\n320:             updates[\"agent_name\"] = options[\"agent_name\"]\n321:         if options.get(\"language\"):\n322:             updates[\"language\"] = options[\"language\"]\n323:         if options.get(\"entrypoint\"):\n324:             updates[\"entrypoint\"] = options[\"entrypoint\"]\n325:         if options.get(\"port\"):\n326:             updates[\"port\"] = options[\"port\"]\n327:         if options.get(\"build_mode\"):\n328:             updates[\"build_mode\"] = options[\"build_mode\"]\n329:         if options.get(\"description\"):\n330:             updates[\"description\"] = options[\"description\"]\n331:         \n332:         for key, value in updates.items():\n333:             setattr(metadata, key, value)\n334:         return metadata\n335: \n336:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n337:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n338:             self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n339:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n340:             self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n341: \n342:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n343:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n344:         if not py_files:\n345:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n346: \n347:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n348:         pom_file = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n349:         if not pom_file.exists():\n350:             raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in Java workspace\")\n351: \n352:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n353:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n354:             self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n355:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n356:             self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n357: \n358:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n359:         requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n360:         if requirements_file.exists():\n361:             pass\n362: \n363:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n364:         pass\n365: \n366:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n367:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n368:         if dockerfile_path.exists():\n369:             return dockerfile_path\n370:         \n371:         content = \"\"\n372:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n373:             content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n374:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n375:             content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n376:         \n377:         dockerfile_path.write_text(content)\n378:         return dockerfile_path\n379: \n380:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n381:         return f'''FROM python:3.10-slim\n382: WORKDIR /app\n383: COPY requirements.txt .\n384: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n385: COPY . .\n386: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n387: CMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n388: '''\n389: \n390:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n391:         return f'''FROM maven:3.8-openjdk-17 as build\n392: WORKDIR /app\n393: COPY pom.xml .\n394: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n395: COPY . .\n396: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n397: FROM openjdk:17-slim\n398: WORKDIR /app\n399: COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n400: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n401: CMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n402: '''\n403: \n404:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n405:         if dockerfile_path:\n406:             metadata.image = {\"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path)}\n407:         self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n408: \n409:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n410:         if output_path:\n411:             return Path(output_path)\n412:         return workspace_path / \"packaged\"\n413: \n414:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n415:         if language == \"python\":\n416:             main_py = workspace_path / \"main.py\"\n417:             if main_py.exists():\n418:                 return \"python, main.py\"\n419:             py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n420:             if py_files:\n421:                 return f\"python, {py_files[0].name}\"\n422:         elif language == \"java\":\n423:             return \"java, -jar, app.jar\"\n424:         return \"\"\n425: ```\n426: \n427: ---\n428: \n429: ## API Contracts\n430: \n431: ### Command Interface\n432: \n433: | Command | Arguments | Description |\n434: |---------|-----------|-------------|\n435: | `pack` | `-f/--workspace` (default: `.`) | Path to agent workspace directory |\n436: | | `--agent-name` | Override agent name (Optional) |\n437: | | `--language` | Programming language: python, java (Optional) |\n438: | | `--entrypoint` | Override entrypoint command (Optional) |\n439: | | `--port` | Port to expose in Dockerfile (Optional, int) |\n440: | | `--build-mode` | Build strategy: local or cloud (Optional) |\n441: | | `--description` | Agent description (Optional) |\n442: | | `--output` | Output path for packaged workspace (Optional) |\n443: | | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging (bool, default: False) |\n444: \n445: ### Typer Command Signature\n446: \n447: ```python\n448: @app.command()\n449: def pack(\n450:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n451:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n452:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n453:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n454:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n455:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n456:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n457:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n458:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n459: ) -> None:\n460:     \"\"\"Validate and prepare agent workspace for building.\"\"\"\n461:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n462:     \n463:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n464:     options = {\n465:         \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n466:         \"language\": language,\n467:         \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n468:         \"port\": port,\n469:         \"build_mode\": build_mode,\n470:         \"description\": description,\n471:         \"output\": output,\n472:     }\n473:     \n474:     try:\n475:         with Progress(\n476:             SpinnerColumn(),\n477:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n478:         ) as progress:\n479:             task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n480:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose)\n481:             result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n482:         \n483:         console.print(f\"[green]Success![/green] Agent [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold] packed.\")\n484:         console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n485:         console.print(f\"  Metadata:  {result['metadata_path']}\")\n486:         if result['dockerfile_path']:\n487:             console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n488:     except Exception as e:\n489:         _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### Metadata File Format\n493: \n494: ```yaml\n495: agent_name: my-agent\n496: description: Example agent\n497: language: python\n498: entrypoint: python, main.py\n499: port: 8080\n500: build_mode: local\n501: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n502: version: null\n503: image:\n504:   dockerfile_path: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ## Error Handling\n510: \n511: ### Exit Codes\n512: \n513: | Code | Condition | Error Message |\n514: |------|-----------|---------------|\n515: | `1` | Workspace does not exist | `Workspace directory does not exist: {path}` |\n516: | `1` | Workspace is not a directory | `Workspace path is not a directory: {path}` |\n517: | `1` | No Python files in workspace | `No Python files found in workspace` |\n518: | `1` | No pom.xml in Java workspace | `No pom.xml found in Java workspace` |\n519: | `1` | Invalid language | Pydantic validation error |\n520: | `1` | Invalid build_mode | Pydantic validation error |\n521: | `1` | Invalid port range | Pydantic validation error |\n522: | `1` | PackRuntime.pack raises | `Error packaging agent: {e}` (with traceback if verbose) |\n523: \n524: ### Error Handler Implementation\n525: \n526: ```python\n527: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n528:     from rich.console import Console\n529:     console = Console()\n530:     \n531:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n532:     if verbose:\n533:         import traceback\n534:         console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n535:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ---\n539: \n540: ## Testing Strategy\n541: \n542: ### Unit Tests\n543: \n544: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n545: |-----------|-------|----------|\n546: | `test_pack_valid_python_workspace` | Valid Python workspace with main.py | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n547: | `test_pack_valid_java_workspace` | Valid Java workspace with pom.xml | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n548: | `test_pack_missing_workspace` | Non-existent path | ValueError \"Workspace directory does not exist\" |\n549: | `test_pack_not_directory` | File path instead of directory | ValueError \"Workspace path is not a directory\" |\n550: | `test_pack_python_no_py_files` | Directory with no .py files | ValueError \"No Python files found\" |\n551: | `test_pack_java_no_pom` | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError \"No pom.xml found\" |\n552: | `test_pack_override_agent_name` | `--agent-name custom-name` | metadata.agent_name == \"custom-name\" |\n553: | `test_pack_override_language` | `--language java` | metadata.language == \"java\" |\n554: | `test_pack_override_port` | `--port 9000` | metadata.port == 9000 |\n555: | `test_pack_invalid_language` | `--language ruby` | Pydantic validation error |\n556: | `test_pack_invalid_port` | `--port 70000` | Pydantic validation error \"port must be 1-65535\" |\n557: | `test_pack_existing_dockerfile` | Workspace with pre-existing Dockerfile | Dockerfile not regenerated, path returned |\n558: | `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_python` | Python workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Python template |\n559: | `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_java` | Java workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Java template |\n560: | `test_pack_metadata_fallback` | Workspace with agent.yaml (no agent_metadata.yaml) | Loads from agent.yaml |\n561: \n562: ### Integration Tests\n563: \n564: | Scenario | Description |\n565: |----------|-------------|\n566: | `test_pack_full_flow_python` | End-to-end: create temp Python workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n567: | `test_pack_full_flow_java` | End-to-end: create temp Java workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n568: | `test_pack_with_existing_metadata` | Workspace with agent_metadata.yaml → pack preserves and updates metadata |\n569: | `test_pack_cli_integration` | Run `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path` via subprocess, verify exit code and output |\n570: | `test_pack_verbose_output` | Pack with --verbose, verify detailed logs printed |\n571: | `test_pack_output_path` | Pack with --output /custom/path, verify packaged artifacts location |\n572: \n573: ---\n574: \n575: ## File Structure\n576: \n577: ```\n578: cmd/cli/\n579: ├── pyproject.toml                  # Project metadata, dependencies, console scripts\n580: ├── agentcube/\n581: │   ├── __init__.py                 # Package version, exports app + runtimes\n582: │   ├── cli/\n583: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # CLI subpackage marker\n584: │   │   └ main.py                   # Typer app, pack command, _handle_error\n585: │   ├── models/\n586: │   │   └ pack_models.py            # MetadataOptions dataclass\n587: │   ├── runtime/\n588: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # Re-exports PackRuntime + MetadataOptions\n589: │   │   └ pack_runtime.py           # PackRuntime class\n590: │   ├── services/\n591: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # Services package docstring\n592: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py     # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n593: │   │   ├── docker_service.py       # DockerService (for build validation)\n594: │   ├── operations/\n595: │   │   └ __init__.py               # Placeholder (no symbols)\n596: ├── examples/\n597: │   ├── hello-agent/\n598: │   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n599: │   ├── math-agent/\n600: │   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n601: └── tests/\n602:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py        # PackRuntime unit tests\n603:     ├── test_pack_cli.py            # CLI pack command tests\n604:     └ test_metadata_service.py      # MetadataService tests\n605: ```\n606: \n607: ---\n608: \n609: ## Dependencies\n610: \n611: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n612: |---------|---------|---------|\n613: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework with Rich support |\n614: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata validation and serialization |\n615: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML metadata file parsing |\n616: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Progress spinner, colored output |\n617: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK (optional, for validation) |\n618: | `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Testing framework |\n619: | `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mocking for unit tests |\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## Implementation Notes\n624: \n625: ### Metadata File Resolution Order\n626: \n627: The `pack` command loads metadata from files in this order (first match wins):\n628: 1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n629: 2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n630: 3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n631: \n632: If none exist, new metadata is created based on CLI options and workspace defaults.\n633: \n634: ### Entrypoint Inference\n635: \n636: When `--entrypoint` is not provided:\n637: - Python: Look for `main.py` → `\"python, main.py\"`; else first `.py` file → `\"python, {filename}\"`\n638: - Java: Default → `\"java, -jar, app.jar\"`\n639: \n640: ### Dockerfile Generation Logic\n641: \n642: 1. If `Dockerfile` exists in workspace → return existing path (no regeneration)\n643: 2. If missing → generate based on `metadata.language`:\n644:    - Python: Multi-stage with `pip install` from requirements.txt\n645:    - Java: Multi-stage Maven build → slim JRE runtime\n646: \n647: ### Metadata Save Format\n648: \n649: ```yaml\n650: # agent_metadata.yaml\n651: agent_name: my-agent\n652: description: \"Example agent\"\n653: language: python\n654: entrypoint: \"python, main.py\"\n655: port: 8080\n656: build_mode: local\n657: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n658: image:\n659:   dockerfile_path: ./Dockerfile\n660: ```\n661: \n662: YAML dump settings:\n663: - `default_flow_style=False`\n664: - `indent=2`\n665: - `sort_keys=False`\n666: - Exclude `None` fields: `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ## References\n671: \n672: - cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n673: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (pack, build, publish, invoke, status)\n674: - AR-021 — CLI build command (follows pack)\n675: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build)\n\n(End of file - total 675 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","time":{"start":1775869764896,"end":1775869764924}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869764930,"sessionID":"ses_285ea26e9ffeiCsnXPY05fn29X","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1624c0001S1qKKzOOKBROpZ","messageID":"msg_d7a15f3fe001hp36zxFONi18di","sessionID":"ses_285ea26e9ffeiCsnXPY05fn29X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d174f424c51f41a8a78c9de14abf36d8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Project Infrastructure (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` with project configuration\n20:   - Project name: `kubectl-agentcube`\n21:   - Version: `0.1.0`\n22:   - Dependencies: `typer[all]>=0.9.0`, `pydantic>=2.0.0`, `pyyaml>=6.0`, `rich>=13.0.0`\n23:   - Dev dependencies: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`\n24:   - Console script: `kubectl-agentcube = agentcube.cli.main:app`\n25:   - File: `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n26:   - Verification: `pip install -e cmd/cli && kubectl-agentcube --help`\n27: \n28: - [ ] **T1.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py` with package exports\n29:   - Define `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n30:   - Export `app` from `agentcube.cli.main`\n31:   - Export `PackRuntime`, `MetadataOptions` from `agentcube.runtime`\n32:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py`\n33:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube import __version__, app; print(__version__)\"`\n34: \n35: - [ ] **T1.3**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py` as subpackage marker\n36:   - Empty file or docstring for CLI subpackage\n37:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py`\n38:   - Verification: `python -c \"import agentcube.cli\"`\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: Models Layer (ST-2)\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py` as package marker\n43:   - Export `MetadataOptions` from `pack_models`\n44:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py`\n45:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions\"`\n46: \n47: - [ ] **T2.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n48:   - Fields: `agent_name`, `language='python'`, `entrypoint`, `port=8080`, `build_mode='local'`, `requirements_file`, `description`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port=8080`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`, `agent_endpoint`\n49:   - Method: `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> MetadataOptions`\n50:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n51:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions; m = MetadataOptions(); print(m.language)\"`\n52: \n53: ### Phase 3: Services Layer (ST-3)\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` with package docstring\n56:   - Export `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` from `metadata_service`\n57:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n58:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import AgentMetadata\"`\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T3.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `AgentMetadata` model\n61:   - Pydantic `BaseModel` with fields: `agent_name`, `description`, `language='python'`, `entrypoint`, `port=8080`, `build_mode='local'`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `requirements_file='requirements.txt'`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n62:   - Validators: `validate_language` (python/java), `validate_build_mode` (local/cloud), `validate_port` (1-65535)\n63:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n64:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='python main.py'); print(m.language)\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T3.3**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `MetadataService` class\n67:   - Constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n68:   - Method: `load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata` — try `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml` in order\n69:   - Method: `save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Path` — save to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n70:   - YAML dump settings: `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n71:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n72:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService; print(MetadataService)\"`\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.4**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` with `DockerService` class\n75:   - Constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n76:   - Method: `check_docker_available(self) -> bool` — check Docker CLI availability\n77:   - Method: `build_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str` — placeholder for AR-021\n78:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n79:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService; print(DockerService)\"`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 4: PackRuntime Core Logic (ST-4)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` with exports\n84:   - Export `PackRuntime` from `pack_runtime`\n85:   - Export `MetadataOptions` from `agentcube.models`\n86:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n87:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import PackRuntime, MetadataOptions\"`\n88: \n89: - [ ] **T4.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` with `PackRuntime.__init__`\n90:   - Constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n91:   - Initialize: `self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)`\n92:   - Initialize: `self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)`\n93:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import PackRuntime; r = PackRuntime(); print(r.verbose)\"`\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path)`\n97:   - Check `workspace_path.exists()` — raise `ValueError` if not\n98:   - Check `workspace_path.is_dir()` — raise `ValueError` if not\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n100:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_validate_workspace_structure -v`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict) -> AgentMetadata`\n103:   - Try loading from `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml` (first match wins)\n104:   - If none exist: create new with defaults from options + workspace name\n105:   - Infer entrypoint if not provided: Python → `main.py` or first `.py` file; Java → `java -jar app.jar`\n106:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n107:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_load_or_create_metadata -v`\n108: \n109: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict) -> AgentMetadata`\n110:   - Override `agent_name` if `options['agent_name']` provided\n111:   - Override `language` if `options['language']` provided\n112:   - Override `entrypoint` if `options['entrypoint']` provided\n113:   - Override `port` if `options['port']` provided\n114:   - Override `build_mode` if `options['build_mode']` provided\n115:   - Override `description` if `options['description']` provided\n116:   - Return updated metadata\n117:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n118:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_apply_option_overrides -v`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `PackRuntime._validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)`\n121:   - Python: check for at least one `.py` file — raise `ValueError` if missing\n122:   - Java: check for `pom.xml` — raise `ValueError` if missing\n123:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n124:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_validate_language_compatibility -v`\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T4.7**: Implement `PackRuntime._process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)`\n127:   - Python: check `requirements.txt` exists (warning if missing, continue)\n128:   - Java: no additional processing (pom.xml handles dependencies)\n129:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n130:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_process_dependencies -v`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T4.8**: Implement `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]`\n133:   - If `Dockerfile` exists: return path (no regeneration)\n134:   - If missing: generate based on `metadata.language`\n135:   - Python template: `FROM python:3.10-slim`, pip install, expose port\n136:   - Java template: multi-stage Maven build → JRE runtime\n137:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n138:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_generate_dockerfile -v`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.9**: Implement `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str`\n141:   - Template: `FROM python:3.10-slim`, `WORKDIR /app`, `COPY requirements.txt`, `RUN pip install`, `COPY .`, `EXPOSE {port}`, `CMD [{entrypoint}]`\n142:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n143:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_generate_python_dockerfile -v`\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T4.10**: Implement `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str`\n146:   - Template: Multi-stage with `maven:3.8-openjdk-17` build → `openjdk:17-slim` runtime\n147:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n148:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_generate_java_dockerfile -v`\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T4.11**: Implement `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path])`\n151:   - Set `metadata.image = {\"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path)}` if dockerfile exists\n152:   - Save metadata via `self._metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n153:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n154:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_update_pack_metadata -v`\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.12**: Implement `PackRuntime.pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n157:   - Execute full workflow: validate → load metadata → apply overrides → validate language → process deps → generate dockerfile → update metadata\n158:   - Return dict: `{\"agent_name\", \"workspace_path\", \"metadata_path\", \"dockerfile_path\", \"status\"}`\n159:   - Catch exceptions: set `status=\"error\"` and raise\n160:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n161:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_full_workflow -v`\n162: \n163: ### Phase 5: CLI Command Layer (ST-5)\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T5.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` with Typer app setup\n166:   - Create `app = typer.Typer(help=\"AgentCube CLI for agent lifecycle management\")`\n167:   - Create `console = Console()` from Rich\n168:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n169:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube --help`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `_handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool)` helper\n172:   - Print `[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]`\n173:   - Print traceback if `verbose=True`\n174:   - Exit with `typer.Exit(1)`\n175:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n176:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_handle_error -v`\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `pack()` command with all CLI options\n179:   - Options: `--workspace/-f` (default \".\"), `--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n180:   - Resolve `workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()`\n181:   - Build `options` dict from CLI arguments\n182:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n183:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `pack()` command execution with progress spinner\n186:   - Use `rich.progress.Progress` with `SpinnerColumn`, `TextColumn`\n187:   - Create `PackRuntime(verbose)` and call `runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n188:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n189:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_pack_command_execution -v`\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `pack()` command success output formatting\n192:   - Print: `[green]Success![/green] Agent [bold]{agent_name}[/bold] packed`\n193:   - Print: `Workspace: {path}`, `Metadata: {path}`, `Dockerfile: {path}`\n194:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n195:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_pack_success_output -v`\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `pack()` command error handling with `_handle_error`\n198:   - Wrap `PackRuntime.pack()` in try-except\n199:   - Call `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)` on exception\n200:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n201:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_pack_error_handling -v`\n202: \n203: ### Phase 6: Example Workspaces (ST-6)\n204: \n205: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py` example agent\n206:   - Simple Python agent: print \"Hello from AgentCube!\"\n207:   - File: `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py`\n208:   - Verification: `python cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py`\n209: \n210: - [ ] **T6.2**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/requirements.txt`\n211:   - Empty or minimal dependencies\n212:   - File: `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/requirements.txt`\n213:   - Verification: `cat cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/requirements.txt`\n214: \n215: - [ ] **T6.3**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/main.py` example agent\n216:   - Simple math operations agent\n217:   - File: `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/main.py`\n218:   - Verification: `python cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/main.py`\n219: \n220: - [ ] **T6.4**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/requirements.txt`\n221:   - Minimal dependencies\n222:   - File: `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/requirements.txt`\n223:   - Verification: `cat cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/requirements.txt`\n224: \n225: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n226: \n227: - [ ] **T7.1**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/__init__.py` as test package marker\n228:   - Empty file or docstring\n229:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/__init__.py`\n230:   - Verification: `python -c \"import tests\"`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.2**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` with workspace validation tests\n233:   - `test_validate_workspace_structure_exists`: valid directory → pass\n234:   - `test_validate_workspace_structure_not_exists`: non-existent → ValueError\n235:   - `test_validate_workspace_structure_not_directory`: file path → ValueError\n236:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n237:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_validate_workspace_structure -v`\n238: \n239: - [ ] **T7.3**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` with metadata loading tests\n240:   - `test_load_metadata_from_agent_metadata_yaml`: load primary file\n241:   - `test_load_metadata_fallback_agent_yaml`: fallback to agent.yaml\n242:   - `test_load_metadata_fallback_metadata_yaml`: fallback to metadata.yaml\n243:   - `test_create_metadata_no_files`: create new with defaults\n244:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n245:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_load -v`\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T7.4**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` with option override tests\n248:   - `test_apply_override_agent_name`: override agent_name\n249:   - `test_apply_override_language`: override language\n250:   - `test_apply_override_port`: override port\n251:   - `test_apply_override_build_mode`: override build_mode\n252:   - `test_apply_override_no_changes`: no overrides → unchanged\n253:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n254:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_apply_override -v`\n255: \n256: - [ ] **T7.5**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` with language compatibility tests\n257:   - `test_validate_python_has_py_files`: Python with .py files → pass\n258:   - `test_validate_python_no_py_files`: Python without .py → ValueError\n259:   - `test_validate_java_has_pom`: Java with pom.xml → pass\n260:   - `test_validate_java_no_pom`: Java without pom.xml → ValueError\n261:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n262:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_validate_language -v`\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T7.6**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` with Dockerfile generation tests\n265:   - `test_generate_dockerfile_existing`: existing Dockerfile → return path, no regeneration\n266:   - `test_generate_dockerfile_python_new`: Python workspace → generate Python template\n267:   - `test_generate_dockerfile_java_new`: Java workspace → generate Java template\n268:   - `test_dockerfile_content_python`: verify Python Dockerfile content\n269:   - `test_dockerfile_content_java`: verify Java Dockerfile content\n270:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n271:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_dockerfile -v`\n272: \n273: - [ ] **T7.7**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` with full workflow tests\n274:   - `test_pack_full_workflow_python`: end-to-end Python pack\n275:   - `test_pack_full_workflow_java`: end-to-end Java pack\n276:   - `test_pack_result_fields`: verify result dict has all fields\n277:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n278:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_full -v`\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T7.8**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py` with CLI command tests\n281:   - `test_pack_cli_help`: `--help` shows usage\n282:   - `test_pack_cli_valid_workspace`: valid pack execution\n283:   - `test_pack_cli_invalid_workspace`: error on invalid workspace\n284:   - `test_pack_cli_verbose_output`: verbose mode shows traceback\n285:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py`\n286:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py -v`\n287: \n288: - [ ] **T7.9**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py` with metadata model tests\n289:   - `test_agent_metadata_valid`: valid metadata creation\n290:   - `test_agent_metadata_invalid_language`: invalid language → ValidationError\n291:   - `test_agent_metadata_invalid_build_mode`: invalid build_mode → ValidationError\n292:   - `test_agent_metadata_invalid_port`: port out of range → ValidationError\n293:   - `test_metadata_service_load`: load from YAML file\n294:   - `test_metadata_service_save`: save to YAML file\n295:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n296:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py -v`\n297: \n298: ### Phase 8: Integration & Validation (ST-8)\n299: \n300: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify pyproject.toml installation\n301:   - `pip install -e cmd/cli` succeeds\n302:   - `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints `0.1.0`\n303:   - `kubectl-agentcube --help` shows pack command\n304:   - File: `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n305:   - Verification: `pip install -e cmd/cli && kubectl-agentcube --version`\n306: \n307: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify pack command on hello-agent example\n308:   - `kubectl-agentcube pack -f cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent` succeeds\n309:   - `agent_metadata.yaml` created in workspace\n310:   - `Dockerfile` created in workspace\n311:   - File: `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/`\n312:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube pack -f cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent && cat cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/agent_metadata.yaml`\n313: \n314: - [ ] **T8.3**: Verify pack command with CLI overrides\n315:   - `kubectl-agentcube pack -f cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent --agent-name custom-agent --port 9000` succeeds\n316:   - Metadata reflects overridden values\n317:   - File: `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/`\n318:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube pack -f cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent --agent-name custom-agent --port 9000 && grep \"custom-agent\" cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/agent_metadata.yaml`\n319: \n320: - [ ] **T8.4**: Verify pack command error handling\n321:   - `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /nonexistent/path` exits with code 1\n322:   - Error message displayed\n323:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n324:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /nonexistent || echo \"Exit code: $?\"`\n325: \n326: - [ ] **T8.5**: Run all tests with coverage\n327:   - `pytest cmd/cli/tests -v` passes\n328:   - Coverage > 80% for `pack_runtime.py`, `metadata_service.py`, `main.py`\n329:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/`\n330:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests -v --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing`\n331: \n332: ---\n333: \n334: ## Task Dependencies\n335: \n336: ```\n337: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3\n338:          ↓\n339:       T2.1 → T2.2\n340:          ↓\n341:       T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3 → T3.4\n342:                ↓\n343:       T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4 → T4.5 → T4.6 → T4.7 → T4.8 → T4.9 → T4.10 → T4.11 → T4.12\n344:                ↓\n345:       T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3 → T5.4 → T5.5 → T5.6\n346:                ↓\n347:       T6.1 → T6.2 → T6.3 → T6.4\n348:                ↓\n349:       T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4 → T7.5 → T7.6 → T7.7 → T7.8 → T7.9\n350:                ↓\n351:       T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3 → T8.4 → T8.5\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ## Verification Commands\n357: \n358: | Task | Verification Command |\n359: |------|----------------------|\n360: | Install package | `pip install -e cmd/cli` |\n361: | CLI version check | `kubectl-agentcube --version` |\n362: | CLI help check | `kubectl-agentcube --help` |\n363: | Pack command help | `kubectl-agentcube pack --help` |\n364: | Pack example workspace | `kubectl-agentcube pack -f cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent` |\n365: | Run all tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests -v` |\n366: | Run with coverage | `pytest cmd/cli/tests --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` |\n367: | Runtime tests only | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py -v` |\n368: | CLI tests only | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py -v` |\n369: | Metadata tests only | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py -v` |\n370: | Python import check | `python -c \"from agentcube import PackRuntime, MetadataOptions\"` |\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ## Acceptance Criteria\n375: \n376: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/workspace` validates workspace structure\n377: - [ ] Creates `agent_metadata.yaml` if missing, loads from fallback files if present\n378: - [ ] CLI options (`--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`) override metadata values\n379: - [ ] Python workspace validation: requires at least one `.py` file\n380: - [ ] Java workspace validation: requires `pom.xml`\n381: - [ ] Generates Dockerfile if missing, preserves existing Dockerfile\n382: - [ ] Python Dockerfile template: `FROM python:3.10-slim`, pip install, expose port\n383: - [ ] Java Dockerfile template: Multi-stage Maven build → JRE runtime\n384: - [ ] Saves updated metadata to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n385: - [ ] Rich progress spinner during pack operation\n386: - [ ] Success output: agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path\n387: - [ ] Error output: colored error message, traceback if --verbose, exit code 1\n388: - [ ] Port validation: 1-65535 range\n389: - [ ] Language validation: 'python' or 'java' only\n390: - [ ] Build mode validation: 'local' or 'cloud' only\n391: - [ ] `pyproject.toml` defines console script entry point\n392: - [ ] Unit tests cover workspace validation, metadata loading, Dockerfile generation\n393: - [ ] Integration tests cover full pack workflow\n394: - [ ] `pytest cmd/cli/tests -v` passes all tests\n395: - [ ] Coverage > 80% for core modules\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ## File Changes Summary\n400: \n401: | File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n402: |------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n403: | `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` | Create | ~40 | Project config, dependencies, console scripts |\n404: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py` | Create | ~15 | Package exports, version |\n405: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | Create | ~5 | CLI subpackage marker |\n406: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` | Create | ~80 | Typer app, pack command, error handler |\n407: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py` | Create | ~5 | Models subpackage exports |\n408: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Create | ~30 | MetadataOptions dataclass |\n409: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Create | ~10 | Runtime subpackage exports |\n410: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Create | ~150 | PackRuntime class with pack workflow |\n411: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Create | ~10 | Services subpackage exports |\n412: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Create | ~100 | AgentMetadata model, MetadataService |\n413: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Create | ~40 | DockerService (placeholder) |\n414: | `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Create | ~10 | Example Python agent |\n415: | `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/requirements.txt` | Create | ~2 | Empty requirements |\n416: | `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/main.py` | Create | ~20 | Example math agent |\n417: | `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/requirements.txt` | Create | ~2 | Minimal requirements |\n418: | `cmd/cli/tests/__init__.py` | Create | ~5 | Test package marker |\n419: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` | Create | ~200 | PackRuntime unit tests |\n420: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py` | Create | ~80 | CLI pack command tests |\n421: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Create | ~100 | MetadataService tests |\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ## Implementation Notes\n426: \n427: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n428: - **Metadata file resolution order**: `agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`\n429: - **Entrypoint inference**: Python → `main.py` or first `.py` file; Java → `java -jar app.jar`\n430: - **Dockerfile generation**: Preserve existing Dockerfile, generate only if missing\n431: - **YAML dump settings**: `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, `exclude_none=True`\n432: - **Language templates**: Python (`python:3.10-slim`), Java (multi-stage Maven build)\n433: - **Dependencies**: `typer[all]>=0.9.0`, `pydantic>=2.0.0`, `pyyaml>=6.0`, `rich>=13.0.0`\n434: - **Console script**: `kubectl-agentcube = agentcube.cli.main:app`\n435: - **Integration points**:\n436:   - `MetadataService` — metadata load/save operations\n437:   - `DockerService` — placeholder for AR-021 build integration\n438: - **Error handling**: `typer.Exit(1)` on exception, traceback with `--verbose`\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## Implementation Timeline\n443: \n444: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n445: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n446: | Phase 1: Project Infrastructure | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3 | Pending | 0% |\n447: | Phase 2: Models Layer | T2.1, T2.2 | Pending | 0% |\n448: | Phase 3: Services Layer | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3, T3.4 | Pending | 0% |\n449: | Phase 4: PackRuntime Core Logic | T4.1-T4.12 | Pending | 0% |\n450: | Phase 5: CLI Command Layer | T5.1, T5.2, T5.3, T5.4, T5.5, T5.6 | Pending | 0% |\n451: | Phase 6: Example Workspaces | T6.1-T6.4 | Pending | 0% |\n452: | Phase 7: Unit Tests | T7.1-T7.9 | Pending | 0% |\n453: | Phase 8: Integration & Validation | T8.1-T8.5 | Pending | 0% |\n454: \n455: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/45 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 455 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Project Infrastructure (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` with project configuration\n  - Project name: `kubectl-agentcube`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775869764898,"end":1775869764927}}}}
